\section{Introduction}

This document demonstrates all features of the \texttt{lpmresonance} package for drawing lattice paths using the PythonTeX integration.

\section{Lattice Paths from Bit Strings}

\subsection{Basic Lattice Path}

Declare a lattice path from a bit string (0=right, 1=up) and draw it:

\begin{minted}[fontsize=\small]{latex}
\lpDeclarePath{S1}{0010011001}
\drawLatticePath{S1}
\end{minted}

\begin{center}
\begin{tikzpicture}
  \lpDeclarePath{S1}{0010011001}
  \drawLatticePath{S1}
  \drawGrid{S1}
\end{tikzpicture}
\quad
\begin{tikzpicture}
  \lpDeclarePath{S1}{0010011001}
  \drawLatticePath[lplpath/label upmarks]{S1}
  \drawGrid{S1}
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{center}

With \texttt{lplpath/label upmarks} option, the right diagram shows upmark labels.

