\subsection{Inside Corner Highlighting}

Inside corners (East→North transitions) can be highlighted selectively:

\begin{minted}[fontsize=\small]{latex}
\lpDeclarePath{IC}}{10010010}
\drawLatticePath[thick, red]{IC}
% Highlight specific inside corners
\highlightInsideCorner[red{IC}{1}  % First corner
\highlightInsideCorner[blue{IC}{2} % Second corner
\end{minted}

\begin{center}
\begin{tikzpicture}
  \lpDeclarePath{IC1}}{10010010}
  \drawGrid{IC1}
  \drawLatticePath[thick, red]{IC1}
  % Show all inside corners
  \drawLatticePath[lplpath/show inside corners]{IC1}
  \node[below] at (2.5,-0.5) {All corners shown};
\end{tikzpicture}
\quad
\begin{tikzpicture}
  \lpDeclarePath{IC2}}{10010010}
  \drawGrid{IC2}
  \drawLatticePath[thick, blue]{IC2}
  % Highlight only first inside corner
  \highlightInsideCorner[red{IC2}{1}
  \node[below] at (2.5,-0.5) {First corner only};
\end{tikzpicture}
\quad
\begin{tikzpicture}
  \lpDeclarePath{IC3}}{10010010}
  \drawGrid{IC3}
  \drawLatticePath[thick, green!60!black]{IC3}
  % Highlight both with different colors
  \highlightInsideCorner[red{IC3}{1}
  \highlightInsideCorner[blue{IC3}{2}
  \node[below] at (2.5,-0.5) {Both corners, different colors};
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{center}

